# emOS framework manifest
#
# Each non-comment, non-blank line is a framework path or glob, relative to the
# vault root. `emos update` overwrites these from the upstream source; every
# other path in your vault is user-owned and never touched.
#
# Matching: `*` and `**` match any characters (including `/`). Patterns are
# matched against paths relative to the vault root.
#
# Lines beginning with `-` are PROTECTED exceptions: never written even when
# they fall under an included pattern above. This is how your real config stays
# yours while the rest of `.agents/` is framework-managed.
#
# `.claude/` is a symlink to `.agents/` (for Claude Code discovery) — it is not
# walked directly, so all agent-tooling paths below are given under `.agents/`.

